result.name: Top Grade Hot Pot

reviews.text: Top Grade is a good HOT POT restaurant so far as I had tried plenty. Their staff is help & hospitality very nice. The beef is fresh & most important for hot pot is the soup, it’s tasty!

Terrible service, food was okay. They also cheated us on the bill, not counting the discount of 40% of the bill, even though our food app, i.e. their partner, said we were entitled of the discount. Instead they told us an excuse as to why I didn't apply at all. So, yeah, terrible.
Food quality is good, but service is below average
Nice place. You definitely need to book, and stay there at least 2-2,5 hours for better experience

We visited on a sunday evening and had a very good experience. The highlights were :

- Great selection of condiments to make the dipping sauce. 
- They have an english menu.
- Comfortable setting (they have comfortable booths). 
- Not too expensive (cost us 826 HKD for two, including tea, two Tsin Tao beers and the service charge).
- Lots of choices (large selection of seafood, dumplings, veggies and meats).

reviews.text: 上品牛肉拼盤一次過食曬7款唔同部位，牛味濃郁又鮮嫩！四川麻辣湯底好惹味！刺身好鮮美！

海鮮拼盤$488真心抵食!! 有6款海鮮，仲有一條活海魚!!
所有海鮮都好新鮮，食得出唔係雪藏貨或者死貨
手切牛肉都好好食，肉質唔會鞋口，有濃郁牛肉味!!

想起火鍋，不其然就想起這一家 ！
配式多樣 ！
手工火鍋配料新鮮、精緻。
海鮮即叫即劏，價錢平宜 。
小食出色 ！
價錢合理 ！
